===== Common callback ====
before_save 
after_update
==========================
- With callbacks it possible to write code that will run whenever an Active Record obj is created, saved, updated, deleted, 
- after_save runs both on create and update, but always AFTER the more specific callbacks after_create and after_update, no matter the order
- after_initialize : using new or when record loaded from database
	after_find : when record loaded from database
	----- after_find call first -----
-after_touch :can you with belongs_to

=====Relational callback====
after_destroy

